N
\ast
    \{N=n\}= \{ U_1+\cdots+U_{n-1} < 1, U_1+\cdots+U_{n-1}  + U_n \geqslant 1 \} 
    \mathbb{P}\left(N=n\right) = \mathbb{P}\left( U_1+\cdots+U_{n-1} < 1, U_1+\cdots+U_{n-1}  + U_n \geqslant 1 \right) = \frac{1}{n \cdot (n-2)!} \tag{$\ast$} 
    \mathbb{E}\left(N\right) = \sum_{n=2}^\infty n \frac{1}{n \cdot (n-2)!} = \mathrm{e} \approx 2.71828 > 2 
